37. How to Access Your ADP Time and Attendance Account Online 

Accessing your ADP Time and Attendance account online can save you time and increase convenience. As an employee with payroll managed by ADP, you have easy access to your account with just a few easy steps. In this article, we'll walk you through the process of accessing your ADP Time and Attendance account online.

Step 1 - Navigate to the ADP Portal

The first step in accessing your ADP Time and Attendance account online is to navigate to the ADP Portal. You can do this by typing in the following web address into your browser: https://portal.adp.com. Once you arrive on this page, you will be prompted to enter your user ID and password.

Step 2 - Enter Your User ID and Password

To access your ADP Time and Attendance account online, you will need to enter your user ID and password on the ADP Portal. Your user ID will be assigned by your employer, and your password will be a unique combination of letters, numbers, and special characters.

If you are having trouble accessing your account due to an incorrect user ID or password, you can click on the "Forgot Your User ID/Password?" link on the login page to reset your credentials.

Step 3 - Click on the "Time and Attendance" Tab

After successfully logging in to the ADP Portal, you will be taken to your account dashboard. From here, you can navigate to your Time and Attendance account by clicking on the "Time and Attendance" tab located in the top left-hand corner of the screen.

Step 4 - Review Your Time and Attendance Information

Once you have accessed your ADP Time and Attendance account online, you will be able to review various pieces of information related to your time and attendance. This may include your current total hours worked, your vacation and sick time balances, and any other accrued time-off benefits.

You may also be able to view your time and attendance schedule or request time off directly from the ADP portal.

Step 5 - Log Out When Finished

After you have finished reviewing your time and attendance information, it's important to log out of your ADP account. This helps to protect your sensitive information and ensure that no one else can access your account without your permission.

To log out of your ADP Time and Attendance account online, simply click on the "Logout" button located in the top right-hand corner of the screen.

Conclusion

Accessing your ADP Time and Attendance account online can be a quick and easy way to review your time and attendance information from anywhere with an internet connection. By following the above steps, you can easily log in to your account and access the various features and reports available to you. If you have any questions or need assistance with accessing your ADP Time and Attendance account online, be sure to contact your employer's HR department or ADP's customer support team.